            . I live in <placeName id="t18181028-78-crimeloc452">Harrow-alley, Houndsditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-78-crimeloc452" type="placeName" value="Harrow-alley, Houndsditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-78-crimeloc452" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-78-off450 t18181028-78-crimeloc452"></join>, and <rs id="t18181028-78-viclabel453" type="occupation">keep a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-78-victim579 t18181028-78-viclabel453"></join>. I had tied the articles stated in the indictment, in a bundle, and put them on a table in the bar. Between four and five o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came into the tap-room, and had half a pint of beer, she then went into the kitchen-customers sometimes go there; I missed her, and thought she was gone. In about twenty minutes she pushed by me, and went out with the bundle under her arm - She was immediately brought back with them. She did not drink her beer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18181028-78-person581">
                  ABRAHAM 
                  MENDES
               <interp inst="t18181028-78-person581" type="surname" value="MENDES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18181028-78-person581" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18181028-78-person581" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was standing at the prosecutrix's door, saw the prisoner with the bundle, and secured her with it, within a few yards of the house. The prosecutrix claimed the property.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I fell asleep in the tap-room, the bundle laid by me, and the prosecutrix charged me with stealing it.</p>
               <p>
